t of England 2016","meanings":["English:  see  Fulthorpe  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Fulthorpe","meanings":["English: locative name from Fulthorpe in Grindon by Stockton on Tees (Durham)."]}]},{"name":"Ellen","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally a variant of   Helen  , although now no longer associated with that name. Initial <i>H-</i> tended to be added and dropped rather capriciously, leading to many doublets (  compare for example  Esther   and   Hester  ). It is also sometimes used as a short form of   Eleanor  , to which, however, it is unrelated."],"variants":[{"name":"Eleanor","meanings":["From an Old French respelling of the Old Provençal name <i>Alienor</i>. This has sometimes been taken as a derivative of   Helen  , but it is more probably of Germanic derivation (the first element being <i>ali</i> ‘other, foreign’ the second is obscure). The name was introduced to England by  Eleanor of Aquitaine  (  1122–1204 ), who came from Aquitaine in south-west France to be the wife of  King Henry II . It was also borne by Eleanor of Provence, the wife of  Henry III , and Eleanor of Castile, wife of  Edward I ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ellen Fulthorp was born about 1488, in Preston, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 son with Godfrey Lambert."},"et":{"ABT 1488–":"umbes 1488–Surnud","1486–Male":"1486–Surnud","1510–1574":"1510–1574","1488–Female":"1488–Surnud","1488":"1488","1510":"1510","1574":"1574","1486":"1486","Abt. 1510":"umbes 1510","ABT 1488":"umbes 1488","Ireland":"Iirimaa","Preston, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Preston, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT 1488–":"noin 1488–Kuollut","1486–Male":"1486–Kuollut","1510–1574":"1510–1574","1488–Female":"1488–Kuollut","1488":"1488","1510":"1510","1574":"1574","1486":"1486","Abt. 1510":"noin 1510","ABT 1488":"noin 1488","Ireland":"Irlanti","Preston, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Pr